OL,3,CCampaigners warn stretch of river is
OL,4,C'dying' due to 4x4s driving through
OL,6,FWatch: Paul Vignaux warns of the
OL,7,Fenvironmental damage caused by 4x4s
OL,8,Fdriving through the Meon.
OL,10,FThe River Meon is a chalk stream
OL,11,Fhabitat, which are among some of the
OL,12,Frarest in the world. Around 85% or so
OL,13,Fare found in England, with most of
OL,14,Fthose in Hampshire.
OL,16,FBut, despite its rarity, the route is
OL,17,Flegally a 'publicly maintainable
OL,18,Fhighway' that falls under the remit of
OL,19,FHampshire County Council.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/14
