OL,3,CCampaigners warn stretch of river is
OL,4,C'dying' due to 4x4s driving through
OL,6,FBecause of this, campaigners say they
OL,7,Fare powerless to help nature recover,
OL,8,Fand worry about the vehicles causing
OL,9,Fdamage each time they pass through.
OL,11,FThey are now urging the county council
OL,12,Fto impose what is known as a Traffic
OL,13,FRegulation Order, which would make it
OL,14,Fillegal to drive through the Meon.
OL,16,FThis could take some time, and locals
OL,17,Fare now pleading with 4x4 drivers to
OL,18,Fthink about the damage they could be
OL,19,Fdoing.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/14
