OL,4,C'dying' due to 4x4s driving through
OL,6,FThe Green Lane Association represents
OL,7,Fmotorised country users, and stressed
OL,8,Fany discussions need to take into
OL,9,Faccount there is a right to drive
OL,10,Fthrough the Meon.
OL,12,FThey ask their members to drive
OL,13,F'respectfully' and follow a code of
OL,14,Fconduct, and say that access should be
OL,15,Fmaintained for all to enjoy nature.
OL,17,FSteve Banks-Smith represents the group
OL,18,Fand met ITV Meridian at the banks of
OL,19,Fthe Meon. He told us that there is a
OL,20,Fbalance to be struck, between drivers
OL,21,Fand the environment.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/14
